        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 5 at 2:06PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 206 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Milliken, or 7 miles southwest of Greeley, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Greeley, Evans, Johnstown, Milliken and Gilcrest.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
